### 5. **SCROLL-RELATED CSS AND JS**

#### Scroll CSS in `/styles/navbar.module.css`:

```css
@keyframes show-down {
  0% {
    position: absolute;
    opacity: 0;
    background: transparent;
    -webkit-transform: translateY(-100%);
    transform: translateY(-100%);
  }

  100% {
    position: fixed;
    opacity: 1;
    -webkit-transform: translateY(0);
    transform: translateY(0);
    background: #ffffff;
    top: 0;
  }
}

.navbar__root__fixed {
  -webkit-animation: show-down 0.5s linear forwards;
  animation: show-down 0.5s linear forwards;
  z-index: 10;
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
}
```

#### Scroll JS in `/components/nav/Navbar.js` (lines 159-177):

```javascript
window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
  const scrollPos = window.scrollY;
  let navbarRoot = document.querySelector("." + styles.navbar__root);

  if (scrollPos >= navbarRoot.offsetHeight + 100) {
    if (!navbarRoot.classList.contains(styles.navbar__root__fixed)) {
      document.querySelector("html").style.paddingTop =
        navbarRoot.offsetHeight + "px";
      navbarRoot.classList.add(styles.navbar__root__fixed);
    }
  }

  if (scrollPos <= navbarRoot.offsetHeight + 100) {
    if (navbarRoot.classList.contains(styles.navbar__root__fixed)) {
      document.querySelector("html").style.paddingTop = null;
      navbarRoot.classList.remove(styles.navbar__root__fixed);
    }
  }
});
```

**Scroll Behavior:**
- Navbar becomes sticky when scrolled > (navbar height + 100px)
- Uses CSS animation "show-down" (0.5s duration)
- Adds padding-top to HTML to prevent content jump
- Reverses when scrolled back up

### 6. **MAIN LAYOUT FILES STRUCTURE**

#### `/pages/_app.js`
```javascript
import '../styles/globals.css'
import 'tailwindcss/tailwind.css'
import DefaultLayout from '../layouts/DefaultLayout'
import { config } from '@fortawesome/fontawesome-svg-core'
import '@fortawesome/fontawesome-svg-core/styles.css'
config.autoAddCss = false

function MyApp({ Component, pageProps }) {
  const getLayout = Component.getLayout || ((page) => <DefaultLayout>{page}</DefaultLayout>)
  return getLayout(<Component {...pageProps} />)
}

export default MyApp
```
- Global CSS imports (globals.css + Tailwind)
- FontAwesome configuration
- Per-page layout support (allows custom layouts like NotFoundLayout)

#### `/pages/_document.js`
```javascript
